result.execSummary:
The defendant Lisa Jean Priante was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fin.Trans.Card-Fraudulent Use (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.41(5)(a)1a.
  • Fin.Trans.Card-Fraudulent Use (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.41(5)(a)1b.
  • Unclassed forfeiture-obedience to office. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

parties.name: Ashland County Clerk of Circuit Court

supervisions.notes:
Def to report to the DOC in Ashland within 24 hours!
If def is placed on probation or extended supervision & owes financial obligations ordered by the Court at the time of discharge, a civil judgment may be entered against the def for all unpaid financial obligations.
  While on supervision the Def is to pay their financial obligations thru the Clerk of Court, which may include payments on restitution, fines, costs, surcharges, etc that are court ordered.
The payments are to be paid directly to the Clerk of Court Office at:
Ashland Co Clerk of Circuit Court
201 Main Street West - Room 307
Ashland, WI  54806

miscConds.notes: All financials obligations placed on a payment plan of $50 per month beginning 9/15/16
Def is to undergo counseling for criminal thinking through a Cognitive-Thinking for Change therapy program.

Not to possess any financial transaction cards unless they are solely in the defendant's name. 
NO CONTACT WITH A.L. 
  The Def is to provide a DNA specimen to the Ashland County Jail within 7 days.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

supervisions.notes:
Defendant is granted credit for time served as calculated by the Ashland County Sheriff's Department.
Granted Good Time.
Granted Work and Child Care Release.
  Def may serve in Iron Co in WI, provided def makes their own arrangements between the departments & at NO additional expense to Ashland Co.
Concurrent with: Count 2

records.addlTxt: Defendant Lisa Jean Priante in court with attorney Courtney J Latzig.  Ruth Diane Kressel appeared for the Ashland County. ADA state has complied with victim rights, def in agreement with state's sentencing after revocation recommendation. Atty Latzig that is the agreement. Atty Latzig/Def comments on sentencing. Judgment/sentence 80 days each count CC, good time, CTS 37, work release and child care release, may serve in Iron Co if SO agree and no cost to Ashland Co. Financial obl in this case paid up.

Attorney Courtney J Latzig in court for Defendant Lisa Jean Priante. Prosecuting Atty Kelly J Mcknight appeared for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Lisa Jean Priante appeared by phone means. 17CM58 PLEAS, 16CM131 probation review (Ruth Kressel appr and representing the state).  Atty Latzig resolved def needs to prepay asks for hearing next Monday for def to appr in person. Atty Kressel wants to do probation review hearing today, asks for extension. Ct comments on financial disclosure statement has not been filed, Def states she may not have gotten it. Ct financially on track, Ct extends 6 months or until completed all counseling requirements.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 21, 2017 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Lisa Jean Priante in court.  Ruth Diane Kressel appeared for the Ashland County. Probation Agent Samantha Hedican appr. Comments by probation officer, Def comments. No counseling completed, PO comments not avail in Iron Co, is now moving to Ashland Co hopefully can complete here. Ct comments on probation until 8/15, PO counseling will be completed by then. Ct, no new crimes, no holds, no negative behavior. Counseling, job, financials, ct is not making changes to her probation. May or may not have another probation hearing  before discharge.
